The paper deals with the mathematical theory of deep convolutional neural networks for feature extraction, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with deep neural networks and their applications in image classification and facial landmark detection. Additionally, the paper proposes new architectures for convolutional neural networks, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
